125
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:06,000
Could it be that the
guy you like is... Jiwon?

126
00:11:06,100 --> 00:11:07,799
Hey! No way.

127
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:08,700
You figured it out that quickly...

128
00:11:08,701 --> 00:11:12,000
No! He definitely doesn't like me.

129
00:11:13,800 --> 00:11:17,000
Right? The one you like
isn't someone else, is it?

130
00:11:19,100 --> 00:11:20,293
Do you know who it is?

131
00:11:20,294 --> 00:11:22,254
He absolutely refuses
to tell us, no matter what.

132
00:11:23,127 --> 00:11:24,567
Is she pretty? No, wait...

133
00:11:25,367 --> 00:11:27,345
Shouldn't you be asking
if he's good-looking?

134
00:11:28,145 --> 00:11:29,200
No way!

135
00:11:29,700 --> 00:11:30,940
Jungwoo is dating a girl.

136
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:39,100
Han Jiwon spilled all my secrets.

137
00:11:40,300 --> 00:11:43,362
Oh my gosh! Kwon Jungwoo actually has a girlfriend.
Are you sure it's really a girl?

138
00:11:43,581 --> 00:11:45,100
Yeah! It's a girl.

139
00:11:45,800 --> 00:11:48,400
Hey! When did you two start dating?

140
00:11:48,800 --> 00:11:49,999
Why didn't you tell us?

141
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:51,301
Aren't we talking about it right now?

142
00:11:51,325 --> 00:11:53,297
No, that's not it. I was talking
about that guy from before.

143
00:11:53,321 --> 00:11:55,676
The one who said they'd only consider
dating you after seeing how you perform.

144
00:11:55,700 --> 00:11:59,700
That's right! Unrequited love just doesn't suit
you. Weren't you really into him back then?

145
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:03,400
I thought so too.

146
00:12:04,300 --> 00:12:05,820
But it looks like that's not the case.

147
00:12:08,700 --> 00:12:12,500
Because someone confessed to me in such a
cool way, I decided to be with that person.

148
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:14,900
Damn!

149
00:12:15,700 --> 00:12:17,940
It's honestly unbelievable that
Kwon Jungwoo got dumped.

150
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:23,015
But to be honest, I already
figured out you had a girlfriend.

151
00:12:23,215 --> 00:12:26,185
Lately, you've been grinning
like you're totally smitten.

152
00:12:26,186 --> 00:12:29,310
- I was about thirty percent sure.
- Hey! Thirty percent? That's way too low!

153
00:12:29,334 --> 00:12:30,386
At least I guessed right.

154
00:12:30,810 --> 00:12:33,732
But hey, is your current girlfriend pretty?
Got any photos? Can I see them?

155
00:12:33,733 --> 00:12:37,293
She must be really pretty, right? After all,
Kwon Jungwoo is pretty good-looking himself.

156
00:12:38,500 --> 00:12:39,940
True, but maybe that's for the best.

157
00:12:40,283 --> 00:12:43,600
You're definitely better
off with girls than with guys.

158
00:12:44,900 --> 00:12:46,301
Is she older than you this time, too?

159
00:12:46,325 --> 00:12:50,276
If we're just going to keep talking about boring
stuff, we might as well head to the internet café.

160
00:12:50,300 --> 00:12:52,700
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

161
00:12:57,700 --> 00:12:58,700
Jiwon.

162
00:12:59,100 --> 00:13:01,710
So this time he's dating
someone older again, right?

163
00:13:01,711 --> 00:13:03,800
- Is she an office worker?
- No, she's the same age as me.

164
00:13:03,824 --> 00:13:06,442
Wow! Same age! Is she from
our school? Which department?

165
00:13:06,443 --> 00:13:10,300
So what if you know? Forget about her, it's
not like you're going to like her anyway.

166
00:13:10,400 --> 00:13:13,400
I'm not interested in
your girlfriend at all!

167
00:13:15,600 --> 00:13:19,100
Wow! Kwon Jungwoo is actually
dating someone his own age!

168
00:13:19,840 --> 00:13:22,560
So, what do you think? Isn't dating
someone your own age even cuter?

169
00:13:22,700 --> 00:13:25,500
Cuter, yeah! But not
because we're the same age.

170
00:13:27,300 --> 00:13:30,500
- It's because she's just naturally cute.
- Stop showing off already!

171
00:13:31,500 --> 00:13:33,300
Come on! Cheers!

172
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:36,000
Cheers!

173
00:13:39,900 --> 00:13:43,300
Ah! But as long as she's
cute, that's all that matters.

174
00:13:44,900 --> 00:13:48,260
His ex-girlfriend was super possessive. She
used to call him out every single night.

175
00:13:48,614 --> 00:13:51,494
If she's just cute, she probably
wouldn't do something like that, right?

176
00:13:52,800 --> 00:13:54,506
Oh, Jiwon doesn't know about this!

177
00:13:54,806 --> 00:13:58,200
That girl Na-jung even treated
us to a few meals before.

178
00:13:58,700 --> 00:14:01,200
Ah, but that older girl is really stunning.

179
00:14:01,500 --> 00:14:04,748
Their skills are top-notch, and you
two make a great team, don't you think?

180
00:14:04,848 --> 00:14:07,400
That's enough, Byun Seung-jin.
It's not fun anymore.

181
00:14:08,800 --> 00:14:11,040
Why even bring up someone
he's already broken up with?

182
00:14:12,400 --> 00:14:15,600
Yeah... what's the point of bringing
up someone you broke up with...

183
00:14:20,700 --> 00:14:22,100
So that's how it is...

184
00:14:26,300 --> 00:14:27,540
You've had enough, haven't you?

185
00:14:29,100 --> 00:14:30,599
It probably doesn't feel fun anymore.

186
00:14:30,600 --> 00:14:31,600
Right?

187
00:14:35,600 --> 00:14:39,500
- Alright! Let's raise a glass! Cheers!
- Cheers!

188
00:14:43,798 --> 00:14:46,124
Hey! How did you
do on this exam?

189
00:14:46,251 --> 00:14:48,039
Whoa! Why are you
asking me that out of the blue?

190
00:14:48,040 --> 00:14:51,239
Weren't we allowed to use our
notes for this test? Did you still fail?

191
00:14:51,263 --> 00:14:52,600
Stop talking about it...

192
00:14:54,800 --> 00:14:55,200
Hey!

193
00:14:55,201 --> 00:14:57,121
When are you finally
going to do well on a test?

194
00:14:58,000 --> 00:14:59,600
Why are you carrying your book with you?

195
00:15:41,300 --> 00:15:42,300
Do you want some water?

196
00:15:46,400 --> 00:15:48,200
How come you're the only one left?

197
00:15:53,900 --> 00:15:54,900
Where is everyone else?

198
00:15:55,700 --> 00:15:56,700
At the internet café.

199
00:15:57,500 --> 00:15:58,500
Internet café.

200
00:16:01,300 --> 00:16:02,300
This late?

201
00:16:02,900 --> 00:16:04,800
Why, you don't like it?

202
00:16:10,800 --> 00:16:11,800
Drink up.

203
00:16:15,400 --> 00:16:16,400
Thank you.

204
00:16:20,900 --> 00:16:22,860
I'll go up and clean up
a bit. I'll be back soon.

205
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:24,000
Take a break for now.

206
00:17:19,400 --> 00:17:21,400
Does seeing the trophy
make you think of the past?

207
00:17:28,200 --> 00:17:30,400
Yeah, a little bit.

208
00:17:31,300 --> 00:17:32,300
I'm not really someone who

209
00:17:33,100 --> 00:17:35,500
reminisces the past that much.

210
00:17:37,800 --> 00:17:38,800
I...

211
00:17:41,700 --> 00:17:44,220
I'm not a very sentimental person.

212
00:17:45,300 --> 00:17:46,900
You really can't tell at all.

213
00:17:58,600 --> 00:18:01,000
Sorry about earlier.

214
00:18:18,800 --> 00:18:21,840
I'll have to keep pretending I'm dating
someone else from now on too, right?

215
00:18:24,500 --> 00:18:25,500
Han Jiwon.

216
00:18:28,400 --> 00:18:30,500
I forgot how good you are at lying.

217
00:18:31,900 --> 00:18:33,600
Sorry, it's all because of me.

218
00:18:35,600 --> 00:18:37,700
I made you tell unnecessary lies.

219
00:18:38,500 --> 00:18:41,020
Don't make it sound like being
with me is something you regret.

220
00:18:43,600 --> 00:18:44,700
I just realized now.

221
00:18:48,500 --> 00:18:50,600
I tend to get hurt easily.

222
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:04,200
Actually... I just thought you were
going to say you wanted to break up.

223
00:19:05,800 --> 00:19:06,800
Me?

224
00:19:08,900 --> 00:19:09,900
Why?

225
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:17,900
It seems like I've made you
upset with all the things I've said.

226
00:19:19,700 --> 00:19:20,820
Just because of that reason?

227
00:19:22,500 --> 00:19:24,700
To say that's the reason
feels like a bit of a stretch.

228
00:19:25,500 --> 00:19:27,500
But it still made you
really upset, didn't it?

229
00:19:29,200 --> 00:19:30,300
But still...

230
00:19:32,700 --> 00:19:34,500
Why would you say something like that?

231
00:19:36,600 --> 00:19:38,200
Isn't that a bit extreme?

232
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:42,100
- Really?
- Yeah! Absolutely.

233
00:19:47,500 --> 00:19:53,100
Do you not want... them to
know about our relationship?

234
00:19:56,900 --> 00:19:58,600
Should I tell Eun-Oh and Seung-jin?

235
00:20:01,100 --> 00:20:04,540
Even though they might seem that way, they're
actually really good at keeping secrets.

236
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:14,840
If you don't want me
to, I won't say anything.

237
00:20:17,200 --> 00:20:18,200
If you're uncomfortable with it,

238
00:20:20,500 --> 00:20:22,300
I'll just say it when you're not around.

239
00:20:43,300 --> 00:20:44,600
Sorry, Jungwoo.

240
00:20:48,800 --> 00:20:50,500
The fact that we're dating.

241
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:54,100
I hope no one finds out.

242
00:21:05,800 --> 00:21:07,400
The way we are now is just fine.

243
00:21:10,800 --> 00:21:13,320
I hope that, in other people's
eyes, we just look like friends.

244
00:21:16,600 --> 00:21:17,800
From now on, too...

245
00:21:21,400 --> 00:21:23,400
Why did you have to
say it in such a scary way?

246
00:21:25,800 --> 00:21:27,840
You could have said it a bit more gently. It's okay.

247
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:31,000
Alright.

